    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not even about wanting to be noticed anymore. it's just that the silence feels more real than anything else. it honestly sounds peaceful, just slipping away without any fuss or any wreckage left behind. like just... fading out. do you think people actually miss people, or do they just miss the convenience of them?",
